RWE’S Gundremmingen Nuclear Reactor Shutdown Showed Fault

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-05-05T16:51:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/rwe-s-gundremmingen-nuclear-reactor-shutdown-showed-fault.html
RWE AG (RWE) ’s halted 1,284-megawatt
Gundremmingen B nuclear reactor showed a malfunction in the
process of taking it offline, the company said.  RWE started to take the reactor offline on May 1 for
maintenance but a water draining device failed to work properly
during tests, according to the operator’s  website . RWE said it
categorized the fault at “0,” or the lowest level of
seriousness.  Gundremmingen is not due to resume power generation until
May 24 and May 26, according to data the utility posted on its
website.  E.ON AG (EOAN)  owns a 25 percent stake in the facility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  